bl ( ) s (Jan 31 22:50 1996   Page 2) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (I\) character container type, charT and the functions whose signature) s nl
bl ( ) s (   has no other types/classes than 'char_type'.) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (     type:      char_type) s nl
bl ( ) s (     functions: assign, eq, ne, lt, compare, length, find, copy, assign.) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (II\) functions whose signature contains other types/classes than) s nl
bl ( ) s (    'char_type'.) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (     not_eof, to_char_type, eq_int_type, get_state, get_pos.) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (III\) defined types, int_type, state_types, pos_types, and off_types.) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (IV\) character constant functions, eos, eof, newline.) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (V\) locale-dependent functions, is_whitespace.) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (Almost all functions in category \(I\), most of which are from) s nl
bl ( ) s (string_char_traits, are needed in iostreams, so thery are expected to) s nl
bl ( ) s (consist of minimul set of the trais member functions.  A template) s nl
bl ( ) s (struct 'char_traits' is for holding such the functions.) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (Different definitions of functions either in category \(II\) or in \(III\)) s nl
bl ( ) s (shall be provided for each of the different character container types.) s nl
bl ( ) s (They are not in the template definitions of 'char_traits' but shall) s nl
bl ( ) s (appear in the each specialization of the traits.) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (For each of the types and member functions, I have made it clear) s nl
bl ( ) s (whether it shall be referred in string class or not, and whether in) s nl
bl ( ) s (iostream class or not.  This cause to make it easy to provide new) s nl
bl ( ) s (character container type.  For example, in case we want to provide a) s nl
bl ( ) s (character container type and its related traits, all we need is to) s nl
bl ( ) s (define the types and functions which referred only in stream class) s nl
bl ( ) s (only.  There is no need to take any care about types and functions for) s nl
bl ( ) s (iostreams.) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (In category \(IV\), both of the eos, newline functions have their) s nl
bl ( ) s (corresponding single-byte characters, '\\0', '\\n', respectively; so it) s nl
bl ( ) s (can be represented as char_type\(0\), char_type\('\\n'\), if every) s nl
bl ( ) s (character container type shall have integral constructor.  Note that) s nl
bl ( ) s (the meaing of both of the characters are locale-independent so we) s nl
bl ( ) s (cannot rely on the locale class.) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (The function, 'is_whitespace', originally introduced to provide) s nl
bl ( ) s (flexibility of the definition of whitespace by preparing it in traits.) s nl
bl ( ) s (Discussion in Tokyo meeting reveals that it cause some inefficiency to) s nl
bl ( ) s (skip whitespaces.  The locale class has now provided a set of member) s nl
bl ( ) s (functions for skipping whitespaces, so the whitespace testing function) s nl
bl ( ) s (in the traits is eliminated with no fear for lackness of such the) s nl
bl ( ) s (functionality.) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (3. Changes made in this specification) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (The following is the exception for the rule not to change any function) s nl
bl ( ) s (signature;) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (1\) [call-by-value interface] There is some inconsistency about the) s nl
bl ( ) s (   character argument in function signatures.  Those in) s nl
bl ( ) s (   string_char_traits adopts pass-by-reference, on the contrary, those) s nl
bl ( ) s (   in ios_traits specifies call-by-value.) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
endpage
