bl ( ) s (## [lib.utilities.traits] Subclase 20.5 should be appended as follows;) s nl
bl ( ) s (######################################################################) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (20.5 Character traits) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (This subclase contains a template class for representing {\\it) s nl
bl ( ) s (character traits}, 'char_traits' and two specializations \('char' and) s nl
bl ( ) s ('wchar_t' versions\) of it.) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (Most classes specified in each of the clause 21\(string\), and clause) s nl
bl ( ) s (27\(iostream\) need a set of defined types and functions to ensure their) s nl
bl ( ) s (behavior.  These types and functions are provided as a set of defined) s nl
bl ( ) s (types and static member functions in the template parameter, 'traits'.) s nl
bl ( ) s (This subclause also describes these functions with the information) s nl
bl ( ) s (which library needs it.) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (In order to specialize for generating an template string or a template) s nl
bl ( ) s (iostream class to handle a character container type, CHAR_T, we can) s nl
bl ( ) s (specify it and its related character traits, TRAITS_T, as a pair of) s nl
bl ( ) s (the template parameters, charT and traits.) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (The struct TRAITS_T represents a character traits related to the) s nl
bl ( ) s (character container type, holding one or more types and static member) s nl
bl ( ) s (functions to be referred in the implementation of such the template) s nl
bl ( ) s (classes.  In order to ensure behavior of objects of the specialized) s nl
bl ( ) s (classes, CHAR_T shall satisfy certain requirements and TRAITS_T shall) s nl
bl ( ) s (holds the set of types and member functions which satisfy other) s nl
bl ( ) s (requirements, these requirements depends on the cagegoly of template) s nl
bl ( ) s (classes \(for example, strings and iostreams\).) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (In this subclase, the requirements common to all of the template) s nl
bl ( ) s (classes whose template parameters are 'charT' and 'traits' are) s nl
bl ( ) s (described.  Those which specific to a certain category of template) s nl
bl ( ) s (classes are described in each clause \(in clause 21 for strings, clause) s nl
bl ( ) s (27 for iostreams\).) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
