bl ( ) s (#######################################################################) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (-- character: In clause 21, 27, and subclause 20.5, the term) s nl
bl ( ) s (   "character" means any unit elements which, treated sequenatially,) s nl
bl ( ) s (   can represent text.  The term does not only mean char and wchar_t) s nl
bl ( ) s (   type objects, but any value which can be repersented by a type) s nl
bl ( ) s (   which provides the definition specified in this clause.) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (-- character container type: Character container type is a class or a) s nl
bl ( ) s (   type used to represent a {\\it character}.  It is used for one of) s nl
bl ( ) s (   the template parameters of the string and iostream class templates.) s nl
bl ( ) s (   A character container class shall have a tribial constructor and) s nl
bl ( ) s (   destructor and a copy constructor and copu assignment operator that) s nl
bl ( ) s (   preserves its value and semantics.) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (-- traits: Traits is a class \(structure\) which represents a set of the) s nl
bl ( ) s (   defined types and functions neccesary for handling character) s nl
bl ( ) s (   objects in any implementation of the string library and/or the) s nl
bl ( ) s (   iostream library.) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (-- NTCTS \(Null Terminated Character Type Sequence\): A {\\it) s nl
bl ( ) s (   null-terminated character type string} is a sequence of character) s nl
bl ( ) s (   type, charT, that precede the termination null character type value) s nl
bl ( ) s (   \(charT\(0\)\).) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
