bl ( ) s (-- underlaid multibyte character stream: We sometimes use byte-stream) s nl
bl ( ) s (   medium\(for example, files, or communication channels\) in exchanging) s nl
bl ( ) s (   character sequense between other entities outside the program) s nl
bl ( ) s (   execution.  In case we want to support such a medium by iostream,) s nl
bl ( ) s (   we represent a character object with a sequence of one or more) s nl
bl ( ) s (   number of bytes, so it can be regard as a multibyte character, such) s nl
bl ( ) s (   a byte-stream medium is called {\\it underlaid multibyte character) s nl
bl ( ) s (   stream}.  ) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (   In streambuf \(or its derived\) class object, we need to convert) s nl
bl ( ) s (   between a character represented in a character container type and a) s nl
bl ( ) s (   multibyte character.  This conversion is performed to invoke member) s nl
bl ( ) s (   functions locale::codecnv facet with the imbued locale object.) s nl
bl ( ) s (   These member functions need a conversion state, represented with a) s nl
bl ( ) s (   'state_type' object, related to the current point \(byte offset\) on) s nl
bl ( ) s (   the underlaid multibyte character stream, represented with a) s nl
bl ( ) s (   'streamoff' object.) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (   When repositioning occur in such a streambuf class object, it) s nl
bl ( ) s (   requires not only the current point but the related conversion) s nl
bl ( ) s (   state, so 'pos_type', which holds enough information to) s nl
bl ( ) s (   repositioning, shall have information equivalent to a pair of) s nl
bl ( ) s (   'streamoff' and 'state_type'.) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (   Implimantation may provide the wchar_t specialized version of) s nl
bl ( ) s (   'basic_filebuf' class which treat byte stream on file as an) s nl
bl ( ) s (   multibyte character string.  In this case, a type 'mbstate_t') s nl
bl ( ) s (   defined in <cwchar>is available as 'state_type'.) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
bl ( ) s (------------------------------------------------------------) s nl
bl ( ) s nl
